snippet.title: So You've Decided To Play Destiny 2...
snippet.description:
Don't worry. We've been playing Bungie's pinnacle loot shooter and have a comprehensive catch-up guide for all new and returning players alike, eager to play Destiny with the upcoming launch of The Witch Queen!

Destiny 2 is a constantly evolving game, so if you haven’t touched it even as far back as the Shadowkeep expansion when it went free-to-play, it might be quite different from what you remember. Whether you're a new player or a returning one, we got you! We breakdown everything from what expansions you need to worry about buying, to how seasons work, and armor builds and exotic tips, just to name a few. 

The Witch Queen is at max hype right now, and this story is about to be incredible with all the build-up over the last 7 years from Destiny 1 coming to this moment. If Lightfall is like Avenger’s Endgame, then Witch Queen certainly feels like Infinity War, and I’m 100% here for it. Trust me, if you haven’t played yet or you fell off, I’m sorry to say that you missed out on some really cool shared experiences but that’s ok! Because you’re back now, and there’s, even more, to discover and experience together, and that’s all that matters. See you on the field, Guardian.

If you would like a written lore catchup on Destiny's story so far, check out Phil Hornshaw's in depth articles here:

https://www.gamespot.com/articles/destiny-the-story-so-far-from-the-black-garden-to-beyond-light/1100-6452481/

https://www.gamespot.com/articles/destiny-2-story-catch-up-everything-that-happened-from-beyond-light-to-witch-queen/1100-6500256/

Timestamps:

Because you’re back now, and there’s, even more, to discover and experience together, and that’s all that matters. See you on the field, Guardian.

localizations.en.title: So You've Decided To Play Destiny 2...
localizations.en.description:
Don't worry. We've been playing Bungie's pinnacle loot shooter and have a comprehensive catch-up guide for all new and returning players alike, eager to play Destiny with the upcoming launch of The Witch Queen!

Destiny 2 is a constantly evolving game, so if you haven’t touched it even as far back as the Shadowkeep expansion when it went free-to-play, it might be quite different from what you remember. Whether you're a new player or a returning one, we got you! We breakdown everything from what expansions you need to worry about buying, to how seasons work, and armor builds and exotic tips, just to name a few. 

The Witch Queen is at max hype right now, and this story is about to be incredible with all the build-up over the last 7 years from Destiny 1 coming to this moment. If Lightfall is like Avenger’s Endgame, then Witch Queen certainly feels like Infinity War, and I’m 100% here for it. snippet.title: Destiny 2 Proving grounds Boss Cheese Grandmaster + Exotic Farm
snippet.description:
Destiny 2 Proving grounds Boss Cheese Grandmaster + Exotic Farm￼

This video is about how to Complete the Proving grounds Nightfall so you can get exotics,masterwork materials and the nightfall weapon Fast as well as the conqueror seal And from July 5th grandmaster nightfalls will be available and you need to have a power level of 1585 to access them
This week's nightfall is the proving grounds strike and in the strike there will be unstoppable and barrier champions as well as arc,void and solar shields so make sure you have the right weapons 
To be able to compete this strike on the grandmaster difficulty you need to have a good build so I recommend to use nightstalker invis hunter with omnioculus,a well warlock with the star fire or Phoenix protocol and for the Titan you can use a bubble or thunder crash
And for the first cheese in this strike is in the tank room and you need to kill alll the enemies before the tanks come out and then go to the far left corner near the door as shown on screen 
From here you can use a well and spawn kill the champions and adds the After that while using a linear fusion you can kill the tank before it even starts shooting at you 
By killing the both tanks first before the 2 champions no more champions will spawn which makes it a lot easier to get a platinum run
And for the boss cheese you can avoid the fire mechanic by standing on the side of the tunnels in the middle where the ledge is as you take no damage here 
And while the boss is in the 3rd phase you can have two players alternate going up and shooting at the pillar and dropping down on opposite sides 
And you can get the new nightfall wepaons such as the horror's least pulse rifle and the D.F.A hand cannon and thesenighfall weapons will rotate
And since this week Grandmaster nightfall the available you can get the adept version of these weapons
and if your not a high enough level you can do the legend or master difficulty and get the normal version of the nightfall weapon 
There is a  guaranteed drop rate for ascended shards and you even have a chance for another one and exotica also have a common drop rate
Watch to the end make sure you turn on 
notifications don't forget to like and subscribe I'm at 2.4k subs ty! let's get to 2.5k subs!!
Thanks for watching 
Also let's try get 50 likes on this video 👍

snippet.title: Solo Grandmaster Nightfall Proving Grounds [Destiny 2 Season of the Haunted]
snippet.description:
Destiny 2 Season of the Haunted - Solo Grandmaster Nightfall Completion / Grandmaster Proving Grounds Solo 1610 Max Difficulty Platinum Rank / Grandmaster Destiny Nightfall Solo Proving Grounds / Proving Grounds Grandmaster Solo / Solo Gilded Conqueror.  Just a video of a solo completion of the first Grandmaster Nightfall The Ordeal this week in Proving Grounds.  Details below.

00:00 - Loadout & Load-in / Entrance
08:01 - Tank Room
22:09 - Power Cores
31:11 - Boss Fight

1 of 6 down, 5 more to go.  This season will likely be the easiest of the bunch, especially considering both the line up and the amount of times each of these have repeated by now.  I've done all of these with cheese, no cheese, no invis in prior seasons - and with us being stronger than ever, it'll be easier than ever.  So first clears will be the path of least resistance, using whatever builds will get the job done quickly enough.  After that I'll redo each of them with different setups when they come back around each week.  Last season I lost track of time with Elden Ring and forgetting that they don't all reappear at the end of the season now (on top of D2 burn out), so this time I'll actually go and redo them each week.  Nothing else to really do in the game until the end of the season this time around anyway, although there's a few other games I do want to check out too.

I'll come back and add timestamps once I'm done with all 6 also.

PC setup:
MSI MPG Z490 Mobo, i9-10900k CPU, MSI RTX 3090 SUPRIM X GPU, 64GB DDR4 3200 C16 Ram, 1TB NVMe M.2 SSD, 8TB HDD

Keybindings and settings can be seen here:  https://youtu.be/ENRkhA9Snvo
